body: I know that shipping Villanelle and Eve is not the most healthy thing to do and all, but to be quite honest, all I want is for them to kiss and have a very wild sex scene next season. Can you imagine how intense it would be? I mean, this show’s photography is extraordinary, Jodie and Sandra have an incredible chemistry, the characters are very attracted to each other, both physically and psychologically. Think about how amazing it was to watch them in episode 1x05, now think about a more intimate scenario, it would be awesome and no one can tell me otherwise. I want to see this for art purposes.

summary: I think about you all the time. I think about what you're wearing, and what you're doing, and who you're doing it with. I think...
caption:
I think about you all the time. I think about what you’re wearing, and what you’re doing, and who you’re doing it with. I think about the friends you have, I think about what you eat before you go to work, and what shampoo you have, and what happened in your family. I think about your eyes and your mouth, and what you feel when you kill someone, I think about what you have for breakfast. I just want to know everything. 

I think about you, too.

blog.description: Welcome to dailyvillanelle! Your #1 source for all things Oksana Astankova (Villanelle) from the BBC America series Killing Eve and the actress who plays her, Jodie Comer. Tracked tags: #dailyvillanelle & #villanelleedit.

summary: Why do you think villanelle is obsessed with eve? And do you think she feels real emotions or has learned to respond to...
question: Why do you think villanelle is obsessed with eve? And do you think she feels real emotions or has learned to respond to situations?
answer:
Hmmm, good question! Umm, I’ll tell you MY point of view or at least the way I see things lol — I think Villanelle is obsessed with Eve because she’s a challenge. At first it was probably about her hair because that was just her first impression of her (any middle aged woman with curly brown hair is gonna catch her attention thanks to Anna) but after realizing that Eve was after her, I think that just intrigued her and she’s been saying since the pilot how she ‘just wants someone to play with’ and boy has she definitely found that person. It also helps that Eve is equally obsessed with her as well so it’s literally a cat and cat dynamic between them. I mean Eve is just as persistent and chaotic as V is, they really are the perfect match in a destructive way.

And regarding Villanelle feeling emotions, ummm she definitely feels things. We seen as much in 107 when Konstantin laid that speech on her and then again during the whole bed scene with Eve in 108 and after Eve stabbed her (that was the most vulnerable we’ve ever seen her so far I think and I feel it was genuine which is probably why she was so surprised that Eve actually did stab her lol). Also Jodie mentioned how we’ll delve into Villanelle’s brain more in s2 and I have no doubt we’ll see her go through every range of emotion because of the aftermath of the stabbing. So while she’s definitely fake as hell majority of the time when it comes to displaying feelings, I still think she has them. She isn’t a robot.

I think there’s potential there to see her be genuine on a consistent basis with Eve since the show is all about their dynamic and I really hope that’s the case because it could be really interesting if done right imo. We see her be genuine with Konstantin a lot and Eve is the only other person that brings out that side of her.
